cs.GT, cs.HC, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.DS 

The paper deals with game-theoretic design of rating protocols for crowdsourcing contests, which involves the study of strategic behavior of workers and the design of incentive mechanisms to encourage cooperation and discourage free-riding and attacks. This falls under the category of algorithmic game theory (cs.GT) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also considers the issue of imperfect monitoring, which is related to cybersecurity (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper proposes a low-complexity algorithm for selecting optimal design parameters, which is related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
